CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 24, 1953, pg. 30, reads: "Celebration of YMCA Week Starts This Saturday - Two No-Trump Bid - Every Thursday a class comes together under the leadership of Thomas Ruffin to learn the intricacies of bridge. The girls, as you can see, take great interest in this form of relaxation. This group can 'dig you' whether you come at them with the Culbertson or the Blackwood convention. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two men, possibly including Thomas Ruffin, and five women gathered around table playing bridge in Centre Avenue YMCA
